message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The discharge, pain during intercourse, and tender cervix suggest a sexually transmitted infection (STI). The green-yellow malodorous discharge and a high vaginal pH suggest Trichomoniasis. Vulvovaginal candidiasis would present with white, curd-like discharge and a normal vaginal pH. Atrophic vaginitis and Chlamydia do not present with green-yellow discharge.

Vaginal pH greater than 4.5 is also indicative of trichomoniasis. Vulvovaginal candidiasis may present with itching and thick, white discharge, while atrophic vaginitis is more common in postmenopausal women. Chlamydia may cause cervical motion tenderness, but does not typically cause frothy discharge or vaginal pH changes.
